title: Works for me
text: Works for me I'm able to use this to time my recovery after exercise. Some more informative statistics would help. Could you bring some of the HRV stats onto the screen please, rather than just reporting 'stress'.   During exercise I hit 100% and when resting get down to 10%.  Why not plot a histogram of the heart rate data or give a number with real units?

title: Love it
text: Love it It does work like their other apps. When I first discovered the apps they offer I used them, and this, to encourage myself to quit smoking. I could see the changes overtime of lower heart rates and lower stress levels.  Only taking a star off because I have to link the app to my social accounts each time I share to them. This never happened before. But it has presented itself as an obvious bug. Though not any reason to not use the app if you desire!   This developer is offering something different here.

title: Cool but...
text: Cool but... It seems cool but, people, don't you find it creepy that it only stores your historical stress levels on THEIR servers and refuses to store locally.  Better yet use your facebook login so 'they' know absolutely everything about you.  Why does it need my location.  My stress is low but our world is scary.

title: Could be better
text: Could be better Note: Phone must have a flash in order to work! This is not mentioned  in the description  or at any point during installation. This is probably why there are so many 1 star reviews saying it doesn't work.  As other people have mentioned, the age input needs refinement. Also, I may have missed it, but I didn't see instructions at any point.

title: SEEMS LEGIT.
text: SEEMS LEGIT. I never knew that my table was so stressed out! THANK YOU SO MUCH for making this app. Now I know that I must take better care of my table. For all you people with stressed tables, I recommend taking it out for a jog once in a while to reduce stress. Also, drinking Chamomile tea is an excellent way as well.

title: Age-ism??
text: Age-ism?? Cool app, but it won't let me enter in a birth year earlier than 1970! If you're going to have option for that, it should be reasonably functional. Dang it...think my stress level just went up!

title: Stressed or Stealing?
text: Stressed or Stealing? They should explain exactly how this works. Otherwise based on permissions it could be just  recording video and collecting data from you. I'm no genius but pretty smart and tech savy. With all the different types of cameras and screens I can't see how this can be legit. That being the case seems to be a data collection scheme.

title: Great, simple idea. Works well.
text: Great, simple idea. Works well. I haven't had any problems with flash heat. It appears to do a very good job. I will have to compare with other pulse measuring methods. It would be nice to get more data--beats per minute, rhythm, amplitude, and anything else possible.

title: Accurate but history log not working
text: Accurate but history log not working Before I review, many people seem to comment about finger getting too hot because of light and not getting a result.  PUT YOUR FINGER ON THE CAMERA LENSE, NOT THE FLASH. Reading seems accurate to how I feel. A little frustrated that the logs are not being stored. Keep getting 'error nul'.

title: FAKE FAKE FAKE
text: FAKE FAKE FAKE This thing isnt real, it measures how much your phone moves and the color of your finger. I took one test and it said 100% stress level , way to high, calm down. Okay, so then i took another. 28% stress level, low and calm, maintain. I took these right after another in the exact same environment, so there was no factor change. My parents were yelling at each other in the second one. Which should have made my stress level the same in the second test, but they didn't. So DO NOT DOWNLOAD ALL FAKE.

title: Love it! Nina
text: Love it! Nina I can monitor my stress levels when feeling life's pressures. When my level is raised I meditate for 5 minutes and take it again and its very low again. Application has become a daily assessment. Very good application and easy to use.

title: Basic
text: Basic Takes a pulse reading from camera sensor. Uses it to determine HRV and gives you a stress level from those measurements. Though no actual imformation on HRV is given and no raw data analysis or r-r intervals displayed to verify it's accurate, like other apps do. All you see is the varying heart rate as the reading is taking place and them an estimation on how stressed you are shown as a percentage. Maybe fun to use, but not all that informative, educational or usefull.

title: No
text: No I am not about to get stressed over some crapp not being able to validate me twitter account. I can see my icon yet it says my profile could not be found. I am sure theybought most of these reviews. It is a useless app. Probably haz spyware.

title: People are so stupid
text: People are so stupid Put your finger on the camera lens not your flash...no wonder your fingers are burnt. Anyway the app based it's result on your heartbeat it could be accurate to a point and always has been accurate with how I'm feeling but if anything its interesting and fun to mess with.  There were instructions on what to do when I did it anyway.

title: Takes too long
text: Takes too long Flash burns the hell out of my finger after about 70 seconds even on a Galaxy S3. On a Galaxy S2 its far worse. Also moving even a tiny bit ruins the test completely. Refine the app to get a more accurate result, faster.

title: False
text: False Iam so stressed it is 3:30 a.m . I have fired a lying, drugged out care taker. And this stress test says I have VERY LOW stress. Don't bother downloading it does not work. ---50 stars

title: A good tool for seeing what helps...
text: A good tool for seeing what helps... I find this useful to see what relaxation techniques help best to reduce stress loads on my body. Note to those complaining about burns: it's not necessary to touch the light, just position your finger in front of it and lightly touch the lens. As long as the lens is seeing light through your skin instead of on your skin, it's good enough.

title: Good app
text: Good app If you do as instructed and lightly hold your finger on the camera lens and hold your phone steady for the full 2 minutes it works great. You can also fix the app (date) to have your age and what sex you are which helps determine your stress level. I use this along with the heart rate app they have. I'm so glad they have these apps!

title: Inaccurate result
text: Inaccurate result I am feeling stressed out of my mind. I figured I'd try this app out, partly to distract me, partly to see what it said about my stress. I gave it accurate age and gender info, ran the test, and the result said I had low stress levels. Not helpful.

title: nice app
text: nice app Works really well and gives accurate results. The picture actually shows how pulse changes in your finger. Guys you have to put your finger on the camera lens not on the flash. No issues with burnt finger. The flash becomes jist a little hot and it's not an issue

title: Love this app!
text: Love this app! The app works very well for me despite being skeptical like many others. I am surprised by its accuracy. When I'm high strung, it knows and when I meditate , it knows I'm not stressed. Great app for learning to relax. Highly recommend! Thanks Dev!

title: This app doesn't even deserve a 1 star.
text: This app doesn't even deserve a 1 star. I was not stressed at all the app said that I'm  extremely stressed. The flash makes your finger so hot and this takes too long of my time doing nothing....

I started the app expecting it to give me instructions. The phone was resting on the DESK. The app explained how it was detecting my heart rate and conluded that I have a low level of stress. What it should have inicated was that I had no pulse since the desk is definately not alive  !

title: Burned out Flash
text: Burned out Flash Don't even think of installing this. Flash failed after second attempt at cooking my finger tip. And trust me it's not cheap to replace a flash on a Samsung Note.

title: Problem Connecting
text: Problem Connecting After installing the Instant Heart rate and app on my Samsung SG3, I figured I'd give this one a try.  This one is not able to display history, change online settings.  Gives me an error Not_found message.  It does keep my age settings, but seems to have a conflict when trying to save or share with facebook.  Good potential it seems.

title: Great idea for managing stress
text: Great idea for managing stress This is a great app.  The only reason I gave it 4 stars is that on my Droid 3 I couldn't keep my finger on the lens because the light got way too hot and it was too painful.  Not enough to physically burn but still painful.

title: Not that good
text: Not that good I am apparently always under a high state of stress.  Even when I'm bored and doing stretches.  I don't get the impression that this thing works very well.  Couple of times it basically said I was off the chart high.  Granted, I was stressed at those times, but really didn't need an app to tell me that.  So this is kind of a waste of time.

title: Cardiac coherence anywhere anytime
text: Cardiac coherence anywhere anytime Once I feel sick. This app correctly calculates my HRV to be too chaotic. After 10 minutes slow rythmic breathing techniques (using my arm watch needle as guide for 5 second breath in and 5 second out), I manage to lower my stress level on the second reading with this app. I recover from sickness quickly in one day. On the opposite need, such as against sleepiness, I use another hyperventilation breathing technique to increase my alertness.

title: My hand is a bit hot
text: My hand is a bit hot And yea. At least I can know when I will stressed.. but my finger is a bit hot later 😂  , thanks dev.. this might not accurate. But I'm still able to aware it when the time is to rest after testing

title: Got to laugh!
text: Got to laugh! Yesterday it's heart monitor have of a reading of 104bpm, today I'm 0% stressed.. I'll be back after an hour on the Xbox red what it says then :-)

title: Proved a big fake..until
text: Proved a big fake..until My kid 5years shows high stress having 55%, proved its just mapped stress% with pulse rate. Feels you real but no such logic exists as I myself working on medical equipments and no such equipment discovered..

title: A load of crap
text: A load of crap It's so inaccurate. First time I tried it I used it properly. I'm not stressed at all and it gave me a reading of 95%. I then used it again but this time I waved my finger in front of the camera erratically making it look like I had a very irregular heart beat, going from very fast to very slow. It then said my stress level was 23. A load of crap basically

title: birth date apparenty stored as "seconds since the epoch"
text: birth date apparenty stored as "seconds since the epoch" Curious that if you try to set your birth date, you can only set it back to Jan 1, 1970.  By coincidence, that's when the unix epoch starts, and unix time is commonly stored as "seconds since the epoch", so it sure looks like the app is storing the birth date using these units.  I'm not sure what effect the age has on the measurement, but if you're older than 42 you can't set the correct age in this app.  The app (judging by the bar graph that represents pulse) also took a long time to get the heartbeat, longer than the author's own instant heartrate app does on the same hardware.  Granted this hardware does not have a LED for the flash, but if the other app can get the HB in decent time...

title: Inaccurate results
text: Inaccurate results I couldn't have been under anymore stress at the time I took my measurements but lol somehow the results were the complete opposite of how I was feeling. My stress level was 2% very low.

title: NHot on my finger
text: NHot on my finger This is a great concept! Im getting "Error Null" when I attempt to save. That's not a big deal for me personally. However there is a problem that's concerning. It takes quite a while for the app to read your finger and the light gets unbearably hot! Ouch! That can throw off the reading and the whole purpose of the app.

title: Very good
text: Very good Wonderful little app which seems be accurate. But it would be nice if you could adjust the intensity of the flash as my finger is usually painfully hot by the end of the 2 minute test. Note to fellow users - don't press to hard on the camera or it won't work.

title: Really cool idea but needs improvements.
text: Really cool idea but needs improvements. The age is wrong, i wont be 22 until next month. The light gets hot toward the end. And i cant log in with my facebook account so it doesnt save my results. :/ awesome for a quick check though

title: Not working any more.
text: Not working any more. Maybe my stress levels are too high (83% last night) but after only 3 uses, app now won't access the camera, so no measurements. Also, unable to retain simple details like age.  Apparently, I'm 0 years old.

title: CONFUSED
text: CONFUSED I thought it was accurate when my stress level was 24% and I was calm. However later I awoke in the middle of the night due to a nightmare. My heart was racing, and I decided to test the app again. It said my stress was 17%...REALLY?! The numbers don't add up.

title: Issue a fix for GPS usage, please.
text: Issue a fix for GPS usage, please. After reading through other reviews, I can say in all fairness that the resulting data is dependent on what phone is being used. This app works correctly with my phone, an LG G2. I do have only one issue with this app:  this app's GPS usage is high, even after disabling my phone's GPS.  Please fix. -1 star until a fix is issued.
